Kumuda (I) — an attendant on Hari.1 Attacked Asura 
followers of Bali.2 1) Bhā. VII. 8. 38-39; XI. 27. 28.
 2) Ib. VIII. 21. 16.


कुमुद
Kumuda (II) — a disciple of Pathya. 
Bhā. XII. 7. 2.

कुमुद
Kumuda (III) — a chief Vānara. 
Br. III. 7. 242.

कुमुद
Kumuda (IV) — a son of Irāvatī. 
Br. III. 7. 292.

कुमुद
Kumuda (V) — a Nāga from Cāndramasa Sāma. 
Br. III. 7. 345.

कुमुद
Kumuda (VI) — a son of Maṇivara. 
Vā. 69. 160.

कुमुद
Kumuda (VII) — a son of Bṛhatī. 
Vā. 96. 247.

कुमुद
Kumuda (VIII) — a Mt. on one side of Meru west of 
Śitoda. Here is the celestial Banian Tree Śatabalū's from 
which flow rivers to Nilāvṛta. The tree would yield what
ever was desired of it.1 One of the seven hills of 
Śālmaladvīpa.2 Residence of the Kinnaras.3 1) Bhā. V. 16. 11 and 24; Vā. 36. 28; 38. 45; 42. 51.
 2) Br. II. 
19. 35; Vā. 49. 32-3; Vi. II. 4. 26.
 3) Vi. 39. 59.


कुमुद
Kumuda (IX) — a Mt. in Kuśadvīpa. 
M. 122. 52.

कुमुद
Kumuda (X) — a Mt. in Gomedaka. 
M. 123. 3.

कुमुद
Kumuda (XI) — a Cakravāka in Mānasa; a son of Kau
śika in previous birth. 
M. 20. 18.

कुमुद
Kumuda (XII) — one of the eight nidhis of Kubera. 
Vā. 41. 10.

कुमुद
Kumudas — a Janapada of the Bhadra continent. 
Vā. 43. 21.

कुमुदद्युति
Kumudadyuti — a Nāga from Cāndramasa Sāma. 
