Kumbhapātras — a group of Piśācas, little in size, hairy, 
brownish in hue;1 are invisible and live on the heads of ele
phants and camels.2 1) Br. III. 7. 378 and 382, 395.
 2) Vā. 69. 263, 274-5.


कुम्भम्
Kumbham — a water vessel, being an adjunct of 
vratams: to be given as gift. 
