Kuru (III) — a son of Manu and Naḍvalā; wife Āgneyī; 
gave birth to six sons, Aṅga and others. 
Vi. I. 13. 5, 6.

कुरु
Kuru (IV) — (Uttara) country of the; famous for a 
forest śaḍvala. 
Vā. 84. 23, 48.

