कृतयुग
Kṛtayuga (also Kṛta) — commences when the sun, 
moon and Bṛhaspati are in one, and the same rāśī. Its cha
racteristic features.1 Form of Hari as worshipped in this 
yuga, and worship by contemplation.2 Etymologically people 
in this age are kṛtakṛtyas. Hari took the form of a vṛṣa 
(bull) for the manifestation of dharma. Hamsa was the 
caste name of men.3 Its duration; repeats at the end of 
Kaliyuga. Pitṛs are worshipped.4 
Physical and moral state of world in; duration 4000 
divine years; sandhya, and sandhyāmśa 108 years; dhyāna 
important in; sandhyāmśa 400 = Prakrīyāpāda;5 after Kali 
