and its purpose. Mucukunda's praise of Kṛṣṇa and request 
of union with Him. Kṛṣṇa replied that he had to undergo 
still one more birth as a dharmic Brahmana and then reach 
Him. Taking leave of the Lord, he saw the advent of Kali 
and entered Gandhamādana. He worshipped Hari in the 
Badarī āśrama by tapas.2 1) Bhā. IX. 6. 38; II. 7. 44; M. 12. 35; Vā. 88. 72.
 2) Bhā. X. 
51 (whole); 52. 1-4; Br. III. 36. 26; Vi. V. 23. 18-47; 24. 1-5.


